Consider this Go Activity designed to be idempotent for a payment system:

```go
func ProcessPaymentActivity(ctx context.Context, orderID string, amount float64) error {
    runID := activity.GetInfo(ctx).WorkflowExecution.RunID
    activityID := activity.GetInfo(ctx).ActivityID
    idempotencyKey := runID + "-" + activityID

    return paymentClient.Charge(ctx, amount, idempotencyKey)
}
```

This workflow uses `ContinueAsNew` every 1000 events. After a `ContinueAsNew`, a previously-completed payment Activity that was scheduled before the continuation is re-executed because the new run replays from a clean event history. Which statement correctly describes the idempotency risk here?
